00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:12,890
Look at this.

284
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:14,630
Oh, shoot.

285
00:14:15,070 --> 00:14:16,739
We only have ten minutes
until we have to meet up.

286
00:14:16,740 --> 00:14:17,780
Hurry, we gotta go.

287
00:14:18,230 --> 00:14:19,230
Ugh...

288
00:14:19,510 --> 00:14:20,510
I can't.

289
00:14:20,690 --> 00:14:22,190
I'm so tired. I've hit my limit.

290
00:14:22,350 --> 00:14:24,549
I've been in these wooden clogs all day.

291
00:14:24,550 --> 00:14:25,590
My feet are killing me.

292
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,150
Ah.

293
00:14:27,470 --> 00:14:29,620
- Come on, hurry up.
- I'm getting dizzy too.

294
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:31,979
- Let's get going.
- Pull me, please.

295
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:33,579
It's hard to walk pulling you like this.

296
00:14:33,580 --> 00:14:34,700
Just hold my hand.

297
00:14:35,590 --> 00:14:37,160
- Okay.
- Okay.

298
00:14:38,030 --> 00:14:39,230
Me too, then.

299
00:14:39,710 --> 00:14:40,710
Huh?

300
00:14:40,910 --> 00:14:41,910
Here, then...

301
00:14:42,170 --> 00:14:43,170
This side too.

302
00:14:43,530 --> 00:14:44,530
What are you doing?

303
00:14:45,030 --> 00:14:46,700
Yep, holding hands.

304
00:14:46,940 --> 00:14:48,770
Alright, let's all go together then.

305
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:51,450
What is even happening?

306
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:52,940
I don't know.

307
00:14:53,410 --> 00:14:56,460
- But it's not so bad.
- This is so embarrassing.

308
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:13,700
Feeling lonely?

309
00:15:14,270 --> 00:15:15,770
- Oh, sorry, thank you.
- Here.

310
00:15:17,070 --> 00:15:18,070
Yeah.

311
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,200
A little.

312
00:15:20,270 --> 00:15:21,470
Because I had so much fun.

313
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:25,230
Me too.

314
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:31,760
Um...

315
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,080
Yeah?

316
00:15:33,590 --> 00:15:34,590
Back at the temple...

317
00:15:34,770 --> 00:15:36,400
That girl we met.

318
00:15:38,170 --> 00:15:39,370
Oh, you mean Anna?

319
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:40,990
Yeah...

320
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:43,980
Um...

321
00:15:44,730 --> 00:15:45,730
Hioki...

322
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,630
Are you two close?

323
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:50,610
Well...

324
00:15:51,290 --> 00:15:52,940
We were close in middle school.

325
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:55,930
But we haven't really kept
in touch since graduating.

326
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:57,920
Why do you ask?

327
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:00,140
Oh...

328
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,600
It's nothing...

329
00:16:02,950 --> 00:16:03,950
Um...

330
00:16:06,603 --> 00:16:08,393
I guess... never mind.

331
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,570
Oh, right!

332
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:17,870
Watarai, hold out your hand.

333
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:19,680
Huh? Why?

334
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:21,960
Just do it.

335
00:16:23,410 --> 00:16:24,610
Here.

336
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:26,050
This is for you.

337
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:27,730
Huh? For me?

338
00:16:28,190 --> 00:16:29,190
Yeah.

339
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:31,180
- Can I open it?
- Yeah.

340
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:36,570
Huh? Why?

341
00:16:38,670 --> 00:16:40,370
How should I put this...

342
00:16:41,060 --> 00:16:42,180
You've been such a huge help

343
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:45,480
these past three days.

344
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:49,220
It's just a little something to say thanks.

345
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:56,790
It's almost time.

346
00:17:02,470 --> 00:17:03,470
Oh.

347
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:04,500
And look.

348
00:17:04,610 --> 00:17:07,100
Didn't you say you have a little
brother in elementary school?

349
00:17:08,050 --> 00:17:09,250
If you don't want it...

350
00:17:09,275 --> 00:17:10,615
- You can give it to him.
- No.

351
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:11,760
I'm keeping this for myself.

352
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:13,500
Okay.

353
00:17:14,370 --> 00:17:15,370
Thank you.

354
00:17:17,233 --> 00:17:18,663
No, thank you.

355
00:17:19,320 --> 00:17:20,350
Tsukasa bro...

356
00:17:21,070 --> 00:17:22,070
Huh?

357
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:24,630
Oh, sorry. I was just copying the others.

358
00:17:24,860 --> 00:17:25,860
You don't like it?

359
00:17:26,570 --> 00:17:27,570
No.

360
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:28,680
It's not that.

361
00:17:29,870 --> 00:17:31,390
You can just call me by my first name.

362
00:17:31,830 --> 00:17:32,790
Huh?
Just your first name?

363
00:17:35,820 --> 00:17:36,820
Call me by my first name.

364
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:39,920
Tsukasa?

365
00:17:46,110 --> 00:17:47,110
Actually...

366
00:17:47,140 --> 00:17:48,740
On second thought, my last name is fine.

367
00:17:50,310 --> 00:17:51,830
What do you mean, "on second thought"?

368
00:17:58,603 --> 00:18:00,003
Alright everyone...

369
00:18:00,060 --> 00:18:01,790
For these last three days,

370
00:18:01,930 --> 00:18:03,200
you've all done very well.

371
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:14,930
Since this is a school trip, please
go straight home and don't wander off.

372
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,050
Please get home safely.

373
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,190
We're heading back this way.

374
00:18:19,780 --> 00:18:21,480
- Bye-bye.
- See ya.

375
00:18:25,420 --> 00:18:26,700
Hey, we're going the same way.

376
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:28,790
Are you heading home?
Oh, I'm...

377
00:18:29,740 --> 00:18:31,890
My older sister is picking
me up around here.

378
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:33,320
Oh, I see.

379
00:18:36,170 --> 00:18:37,170
Um...

380
00:18:40,860 --> 00:18:41,860
Thank you.

381
00:18:42,130 --> 00:18:43,850
For asking me to join your group.

382
00:18:44,940 --> 00:18:45,940
I wanted to say it again.

383
00:18:46,930 --> 00:18:49,280
I had a really great
time being in this group.

384
00:18:49,980 --> 00:18:50,980
Glad to hear it.

385
00:18:51,670 --> 00:18:52,770
Hearing you say that,

386
00:18:52,990 --> 00:18:54,430
I'm really glad I asked you to join.

387
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:56,050
But, uh...

388
00:18:56,340 --> 00:18:58,720
I wasn't actually the one who invited you.

389
00:19:00,010 --> 00:19:01,010
Huh?

390
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,240
Yeah.

391
00:19:06,860 --> 00:19:08,060
Watarai?

392
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:09,730
What is it?

393
00:19:12,230 --> 00:19:13,330
I'd like

394
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,260
to speak with Hioki

395
00:19:16,450 --> 00:19:17,550
for a moment.

396
00:19:26,230 --> 00:19:27,230
Um...

397
00:19:28,950 --> 00:19:30,220
About the first day...

398
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:32,680
Do you remember?

399
00:19:34,910 --> 00:19:35,910
At the hotel...

400
00:19:36,730 --> 00:19:38,170
When you went back for your glasses.

401
00:19:38,790 --> 00:19:40,180
Huh? My glasses?

402
00:19:42,690 --> 00:19:43,690
Oh...

403
00:19:43,860 --> 00:19:44,860
Oh no.

404
00:19:46,100 --> 00:19:47,770
I'll do anything, please forgive me.

405
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:51,250
It completely slipped my mind.

406
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:53,280
That whole thing...

407
00:19:53,890 --> 00:19:55,170
So we're not past that yet, huh?

408
00:19:57,650 --> 00:19:58,650
Yeah.

409
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:00,990
Of course, I remember.

410
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,000
Um, there's something...

411
00:20:04,900 --> 00:20:06,240
I'd like to ask you.

412
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,500
Yeah?

413
00:20:09,470 --> 00:20:10,470
Okay.

414
00:20:20,690 --> 00:20:21,690
Have a seat.

415
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:30,120
Actually...

416
00:20:31,780 --> 00:20:33,620
about the groups for the school trip...

417
00:20:34,910 --> 00:20:36,750
the one who suggested
inviting you, Hioki-kun,

418
00:20:38,430 --> 00:20:39,690
was me.

419
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:42,510
Huh?

420
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:46,600
But...

421
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,650
it wasn't because you're always alone,

422
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:51,610
or for any reason like that.

423
00:20:53,220 --> 00:20:54,220
I just...

424
00:20:54,540 --> 00:20:55,540
simply...

425
00:20:56,030 --> 00:20:57,030
wanted to get to know

426
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:59,190
you a little better.

427
00:21:03,130 --> 00:21:04,330
Why are you telling me...

428
00:21:05,220 --> 00:21:06,560
this now?

429
00:21:10,140 --> 00:21:12,010
Because we'd never really talked.

430
00:21:14,410 --> 00:21:15,760
I didn't know anything about you.

431
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:18,970
I just genuinely wanted to talk to you.

432
00:21:20,770 --> 00:21:21,770
At first,

433
00:21:22,610 --> 00:21:24,140
that's really all it was.

434
00:21:25,770 --> 00:21:27,470
At first?

435
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:33,900
But after actually...

436
00:21:35,540 --> 00:21:36,900
spending time with you...

437
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,690
These past three days,
I've learned so much about you.

438
00:21:45,740 --> 00:21:47,370
Your fun side,

439
00:21:49,070 --> 00:21:50,340
your kind side,

440
00:21:53,340 --> 00:21:55,330
and your slightly ditzy and cute side.

441
00:21:57,790 --> 00:21:59,200
I like all of it.

442
00:22:02,290 --> 00:22:03,490
Somehow...

443
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:05,950
this whole vibe...

444
00:22:08,340 --> 00:22:09,440
it just...

445
00:22:10,290 --> 00:22:11,530
made me want to get to know you

446
00:22:12,230 --> 00:22:13,850
even more.

447
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,090
So...

448
00:22:27,320 --> 00:22:28,620
if you'll have me...

449
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:31,200
please go out...

450
00:22:35,290 --> 00:22:36,730
No way...

451
00:22:37,770 --> 00:22:39,050
Is he about to confess to me?

452
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:43,290
With me...

453
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:54,700
(Next Episode)

454
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:56,106
(After the 3-day, 2-night school trip, )
Hioki...

455
00:22:56,130 --> 00:22:57,136
(their relationship deepens.)
Let's go together.

456
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:58,730
I can't see if you keep fidgeting.

457
00:22:58,930 --> 00:23:00,690
Excuse me, I'm borrowing
Hioki for a second.

458
00:23:00,850 --> 00:23:03,650
(The spark of jealousy ignites.)
I'm so jealous. You two are so chummy.

459
00:23:04,330 --> 00:23:06,360
Just let me stay like
this a little longer...

460
00:23:06,613 --> 00:23:08,723
You're Hioki Asahi, right?
